~ start
Cat: That's my journal, I stopped writting in it a long time ago.
- Page 1
	Cat: "I got accepted to art school!! Everybody told me to choose a normal path, but I wanted to do what I like for once..."
	Cat: I can finally read the blurry parts ...
	Cat: ".. I needed a way to escape the routine everybody has... I don't want to fall into this cycle."
	Cat: "The void... I cant allow myself to fall in it..."
- Page 2
	Cat : "I can't seem to find a stable job in this field, but I don't want to fall into the void of the routine..."
	Cat: " I love art so much, but I fear that if I try to stick to it desperately, I will just worry about tomorrow's bills... "
- Page 3
	Cat: I dont feel like reading today, let's just finish tomorrow
- Day 1
	Cat: I should write something.
	Cat: People always tell you to follow your dreams, but nobody tells you what to do when your dreams don't pay for groceries.
	Cat: So I got a stable job.
	Cat: Eight hours a day.
	Cat: Five days a week.
	Cat: Sometimes I look at my old art certificates hanging on the wall and wonder what happened to that version of me.
	Cat: Today I "accidentally" broke the office printer.
	Cat: Everyone laughed.
	Cat: It was the most alive I've felt at work in months.
- Day 2
	Cat: Today I covered part of the office with paint.
	Cat: Management will probably hate it.
	Cat: My coworkers couldn't stop laughing.
	Cat: For a moment, watching all those colors spread across those dull gray walls, I remembered why I loved art in the first place.
	Cat: Maybe I don't miss painting.
	Cat: Maybe I miss feeling creative.
	Cat: Maybe I miss feeling like myself.
	Cat: The office gets harder to tolerate every day.

- Exit => END
=> END